13/08/2007
ANKARA, Turkey -- Eleven Turkish soldiers and two civilians were wounded in an explosion Sunday (August 12th) in southeast Turkey. Military officials said the roadside bomb was planted by militants from the terrorist Kurdistan Workers' Party (PKK). The incident happened in the Eruh district in Siirt province, near the border with Iraq. The soldiers were in a minibus participating in an operation aimed at capturing PKK guerillas. 
Meanwhile, officials reportedly managed to thwart two terrorist attacks by the PKK in Van province. Local news reports that a suspicious package found under the building housing the local Roads department contained the explosive A4. A similar package found on a street contained the explosive as well. (Sabah, Zaman, Milliet, NTV - 13/08/07; AFP, Reuters, AP, Anadolu news agency, Dogan, Xinhua - 12/08/07)
